AD_FIELD.HELP: Defines the template on which the current template depends.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Component Type
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A type of component for which the template operates.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A type of component for which the template operates.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Active
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_FIELD.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Overrides Template
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Is used to define that this template overrides another template.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Defines that this template overrides the template which is defined in this field. When processing a user interface component request from the browser, the system searches for the template to handle the request. The 'overrides template' field plays an important role in this process. When a template is selected then the system checks if the template is overridden, if this is the case then the overriding template is used. This search step are done multi-level (so if the overriding template is again overridden then the deepest/last overriding template is used).

AD_FIELD.NAME: Template dependency
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Template dependency
AD_FIELD.HELP: Defines a template dependency, that a template depends on another template, i.e. uses functions from the other template.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Name
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A non-unique identifier for a record/document often used as a search tool.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A more descriptive identifier (that does need to be unique) of a record/document that is used as a default search option along with the search key (that is unique and mostly shorter). It is up to 60 characters in length.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Template Classpath Location
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Defines the location in the classpath of the template file
AD_FIELD.HELP: Defines the location in the classpath of the template file. The template is loaded using the classloader. The path must be an absolute path (so start with a /).

AD_FIELD.NAME: Template
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The template used to generate the visualization of the component.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Defines the template which is used to generate the (javascript) code to render the component.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Template
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The template source code.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The source code of the template. This code gets executed when the template is processed. The language of the source code (freemarker or another) is defined by the template language field. Note that instead of this field it is also possible to use the template class path location field to point to a file containing the source cod
